---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const methods = await getCollection('methods');
const sorted = [...methods].sort((a, b) => b.data.date.getTime() - a.data.date.getTime());

const difficultyColors = {
  easy: '#047857',
  medium: '#b45309',
  hard: '#b91c1c',
};
---

<Layout
  title="Gopher Control Methods & Tactics | Mark The Bagger"
  description="Field-tested gopher control methods from easy repellents to advanced burrow fumigation. Mark the Bagger's step-by-step playbook for eliminating gophers from your yard."
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> › Gopher Control Methods
  </nav>

  <header>
    <h1>Gopher Control Methods</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Step-by-step tactics for reclaiming your yard from pocket gophers.</p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="card">
      <h2>All Methods</h2>
      <div style="display: grid; gap: 1rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));">
        {sorted.map((method) => (
          <article style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e4e4e7; border-radius: 8px; background: #fafafa;">
            <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">{method.data.title}</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #52525b; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">{method.data.description}</p>
            <p>
              <span style={`display: inline-block; padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 999px; color: white; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; background: ${difficultyColors[method.data.difficulty]};`}>
                {method.data.difficulty}
              </span>
            </p>
            <a href={`/methods/${method.slug}`} class="btn">Read the {method.data.title} Guide</a>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Passive Defense: Vibration Poles</h2>
      <p>Think of these as your background firewall. Ultrasonic and vibrational stakes aren't going to eliminate a massive infestation on their own, but they are fantastic deterrents when paired with traps or soil treatments. Place them every 30-45 feet and move them weekly so the gophers don't get used to the pattern.</p>
      <a href="https://amzn.to/4c7WkYT" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">View Top Rated Gopher Repellent Poles on Amazon</a>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Precision Capture: Live Wire Traps</h2>
      <p>If you need to relocate the gopher (or if local laws require it), two-door live traps placed directly in the main runway are your best bet. Always wire the trap to a surface stake so the gopher doesn't drag it deeper into the network, and check it every 12 hours.</p>
      <a href="https://amzn.to/4aPIsjG" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">View Live Gopher Traps on Amazon</a>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
